"```sql\nSELECT \n    CASE \n        WHEN COUNT(ID) FILTER (WHERE SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+') > COUNT(ID) FILTER (WHERE SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-') \n        THEN 'In-patient' \n        ELSE 'Outpatient' \n    END AS Patient_Type,\n    ABS(COUNT(ID) FILTER (WHERE SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+') - COUNT(ID) FILTER (WHERE SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-')) * 100.0 / NULLIF(COUNT(ID) FILTER (WHERE SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-'), 0)) AS Deviation_Percentage\nFROM Patient;\n``` \n\nThis SQL query counts the number of male patients who are in-patients and outpatients, compares them, and calculates the deviation in percentage based on the counts. The `NULLIF` function is used to avoid division by zero in the percentage calculation."